{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Description\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This script facilitates "Area selection" and "Area copy"; i.e. moving or duplicating all items and automation in the time selection of selected tracks, including automation from tracks without any items.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The script cycles between\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1)\tx360\tab inserting temporary empty items into the time selection of selected tracks, and\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2)\tx360\tab deleting all temporary items from the project.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 When the temporary items are inserted, Crtl-drag can be used to copy the items and automation to their new position or even to other tracks. Pre-existing envelope points in the paste target area will be overwritten.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Instructions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1)\tx360\tab Select time and tracks\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2)\tx360\tab Run the script to insert temporary items across the time selection\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3)\tx360\tab Ctrl-drag the items to their new position\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4)\tx360\tab Run the script again to remove the (duplicated) temporary items.\sa180\par}
}

