{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Apply render preset\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This package provides two scripts for applying render presets from outside of the render dialog.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The primary action, {\i cfillion_Apply render preset.lua}, shows a list of all available presets and applies the selected one.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The second action, {\i cfillion_Apply render preset (create action)}.lua, dynamically creates a new action script for applying the chosen preset. This new action can be used for applying the chosen preset without any user interaction (eg. as part of a custom action).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The main script and generated scripts can be combined with the REAPER action "File: Render project, using the most recent render settings" (or similar) as part of a custom action.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 Caveats\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The following restrictions apply due to current limitations in REAPER's scripting API.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 These settings are applied but not visible immediately in the render dialog (if opened):\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Render speed\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Resample mode\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 These settings are NOT applied:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Use project sample rate for mixing and FX/synth processing\sa180\par}
}

