{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 Split at transients and create regions named from pitches\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Overview\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 I created this script to assist me in chopping and exporting samples of pitched instruments for importing into Kontakt or hardware sampler synths.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In a nutshell, you can record a bunch of notes from your source into one, long audio file and this script will split the recording at the transients.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Next, it will shorten each part by the amount you specify, and apply a logarithmic fade-out to each part of the duration you specify.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But wait, there's more: it will then bounce each audio part to a MIDI take at high-speed and "de-noise" the resulting MIDI part by deleting any notes that are shorter than the duration you specify. This prepares the groundwork for the next processing phase...\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 ...wherein a region is created for each note part, with the region name consisting of the note name and an ordinal number. For example, if you recorded three C#'s in the 2nd octave and an F# in the 3rd octave, the regions would be named {\b C#2_1}, {\b C#2_2}, {\b C#2_3} and {\b F#3_1}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Finally, it will automatically enable these regions in the Render Matrix for the parent track.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 All of these actions are encapsulated in a single undo point so that you can easily try different settings until you achieve the desired results.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 At this point, you can go into the Region Render Matrix and render out your individual sample files, all named according to pitch.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Dependencies\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://sws-extension.org/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
SWS Extension
}}}
 (used for splitting at transients)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Setup\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab {\b Required:} Ensure you have a saved ReaTune preset with the {\b Send MIDI events when pitch changes} box checked. Leave all the other options in ReaTune at their default values. (This step will be required until such time as the API allows ReaTune parameters to be set at run-time).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab {\b Recommended}: Create a Render Matrix preset to name your rendered files using wild cards, for example: $project\\$track\\$region\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Configuration\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You can change the values of the following constants in the USER CONFIG AREA section of the script to achieve optimum results:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 uc_reatune_midi_out_preset_name = "NoCorrection_OutputPitchMIDI"\line
uc_autofade_seconds = 1\line
uc_trim_end_seconds = 1\line
uc_note_min_seconds = 1\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Instructions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Ensure {\b Setup} is complete\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Drag your audio file into Arrange Window to create a track\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Select the audio item\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Run the script\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Go to {\b View/Region Render Matrix}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 6.\tx360\tab Click {\b Render}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 7.\tx360\tab Select your render preset or enter desired settings\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 8.\tx360\tab Click {\b Render xx files..} button\sa180\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Tool that shows cursor position in relation to the item take's Source time\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab remembers last position and window size\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab resizeable via mouse-wheel\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab edit cursor can be moved to any user-defined source time position\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab directory where source file resides can be opened in explorer/finder\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab tooltips\sa180\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Track Tags\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This script is based on Tracktion 6 track tags\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 Screenshot\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 https://forum.cockos.com/showpost.php?p=1956530&postcount=1\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 Main Features\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Show and hide tagged track groups from TCP/MCP\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 Known Issues/Limitations\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab This is an alpha version\sa180\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 tompad_MusicMath is a reascript to get ms from bpm and Hz from pitch in a Reaperproject.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 When script window is opened, it takes the current bpm from Reaper and by choosing note buttons it convert bpm to ms.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 By clicking the resulting ms-text the script is copying the ms to the systems clipboard (for pasting in to delay f.ex)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Any comments on coding, requests, bugs etc is welcome! PM me (tompad) on Reaper Forum (https://forum.cockos.com/member.php?u=19103).\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 tompad_obliques\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 tompad_obliques is a reascript that randomly shows text from Oblique Strategies by Brian Eno and Peter Schmidt.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Any comments on coding, requests, bugs etc is welcome! PM me (tompad) on Reaper Forum (https://forum.cockos.com/member.php?u=19103).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Credits Oblique Strategies by Brian Eno and Peter Schmidt\par}
}

